        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The date is established by the relationship between this letter and the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-13718.xml">letter from Jules Barrois, 6 March [1882]</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">On the founding of the laboratory at Villefranche-sur-Mer, see <ref target="./DCP-LETT-13718.xml">letter from Jules Barrois, 6 March [1882]</ref> and n. 3. <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1346.xml">Anton Dohrn</ref> had founded the Marine Zoological Station at Naples in 1872. On CD’s support for the station, see, for example, <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1581.xml"><hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi></ref> vol. 20, <ref target="./DCP-LETT-8486.xml">letter to Anton Dohrn, 24 August [1872]</ref>. <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_2777.xml">Henri de Lacaze-Duthiers</ref> had founded the Roscoff Biological Station on the northern coast of Brittany in 1872, and the Laboratoire Arago (Oceanological Observatory at Banyuls-sur-Mer) on the Mediterranean coast of France in 1881 (<hi rend="italic">Science</hi>, 9 July 1886, pp. 27–8).</note> 
        </div>
    
